<section id="typography" class="pl-section o-container">
  <h2 class="pl-heading">Typography</h2>
  <p class="pl-description">Headings use <strong>DM Serif Display</strong> (serif). Body copy uses <strong>Source Sans 3</strong> (sans-serif). The type scale follows a Major Third ratio (1.25&times;).</p>

  <h3 class="pl-subheading">Headings</h3>
  <div class="pl-specimen">
    <div class="pl-type-sample">
      <h1 style="margin-block-end: 0">Heading 1 &mdash; DM Serif Display</h1>
      <div class="pl-type-meta">--text-5xl / 3.75rem &middot; font-weight: 700 &middot; line-height: 1.2</div>
    </div>
    <div class="pl-type-sample">
      <h2 style="margin-block-end: 0">Heading 2 &mdash; Rail Safety Across the Network</h2>
      <div class="pl-type-meta">--text-4xl (fluid) &middot; font-weight: 700</div>
    </div>
    <div class="pl-type-sample">
      <h3 style="margin-block-end: 0">Heading 3 &mdash; Community Partnerships</h3>
      <div class="pl-type-meta">--text-xl / 1.5rem &middot; font-weight: 700</div>
    </div>
    <div class="pl-type-sample">
      <h4 style="margin-block-end: 0">Heading 4 &mdash; School Engagement</h4>
      <div class="pl-type-meta">--text-lg / 1.25rem &middot; font-weight: 700</div>
    </div>
    <div class="pl-type-sample">
      <h5 style="margin-block-end: 0">Heading 5 &mdash; Key Partners</h5>
      <div class="pl-type-meta">--text-md / 1.125rem &middot; Source Sans 3 &middot; font-weight: 600</div>
    </div>
    <div class="pl-type-sample" style="border: none; padding-block-end: 0; margin-block-end: 0">
      <h6 style="margin-block-end: 0">Heading 6 &mdash; Resources</h6>
      <div class="pl-type-meta">--text-base / 1rem &middot; Source Sans 3 &middot; uppercase &middot; font-weight: 600</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 class="pl-subheading">Body Copy</h3>
  <div class="pl-specimen">
    <p>This is a standard body paragraph using Source Sans 3 at <code>--text-base</code> (1rem / 16px) with a line height of 1.6. Body copy is capped at 68 characters wide for comfortable reading. Travel Safe Travel Smart supports communities across the UK by promoting railway safety, preventing harm and strengthening local partnerships.</p>
    <p>A second paragraph follows naturally. We work directly with schools, colleges, community groups, local authorities and partner agencies to help people understand the risks around the railway and encourage safer behaviour.</p>
  </div>

  <h3 class="pl-subheading">Inline Elements</h3>
  <div class="pl-specimen">
    <p>
      This text contains a <a href="#">hyperlink to another page</a>,
      some <strong>bold text</strong>,
      some <em>italic text</em>,
      some <code>inline code</code>,
      a <mark>highlighted phrase</mark>,
      and <small>small text for disclaimers</small>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h3 class="pl-subheading">Blockquote</h3>
  <div class="pl-specimen">
    <blockquote>
      <p>The session was brilliant &mdash; the children were completely engaged and are still talking about it weeks later. It's made a real difference to how they think about the railway.</p>
      <footer>&mdash; Year 5 teacher, Tonbridge Primary School</footer>
    </blockquote>
  </div>

  <h3 class="pl-subheading">Lists</h3>
  <div class="pl-specimen">
    <div class="o-grid o-grid--2">
      <div>
        <p class="pl-label">Unordered</p>
        <ul>
          <li>School sessions</li>
          <li>Youth organisations</li>
          <li>Station visits</li>
          <li>Digital resources</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="pl-label">Ordered</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Identify hotspot locations</li>
          <li>Assess risk with partners</li>
          <li>Deliver targeted intervention</li>
          <li>Monitor and evaluate impact</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 class="pl-subheading">Code Block</h3>
  <div class="pl-specimen">
    <pre><code>// Eleventy config example
module.exports = function (eleventyConfig) {
  eleventyConfig.addPassthroughCopy("assets");
  return {
    templateFormats: ["njk", "md"],
    dir: { input: "src", output: "_site" }
  };
};</code></pre>
  </div>
</section>


{# =====================================================================
   3. SPACING
   ===================================================================== #}

<section id="spacing" class="pl-section o-container">
  <h2 class="pl-heading">Spacing Scale</h2>
  <p class="pl-description">An 8px-based scale from <code>--space-1</code> (4px) to <code>--space-32</code> (128px). Fluid variants use <code>clamp()</code> for responsive spacing.</p>

  <div class="pl-specimen">
    {% set spacingTokens = [
      { name: "--space-1",  value: "0.25rem (4px)" },
      { name: "--space-2",  value: "0.5rem (8px)" },
      { name: "--space-3",  value: "0.75rem (12px)" },
      { name: "--space-4",  value: "1rem (16px)" },
      { name: "--space-6",  value: "1.5rem (24px)" },
      { name: "--space-8",  value: "2rem (32px)" },
      { name: "--space-10", value: "2.5rem (40px)" },
      { name: "--space-12", value: "3rem (48px)" },
      { name: "--space-16", value: "4rem (64px)" },
      { name: "--space-20", value: "5rem (80px)" },
      { name: "--space-24", value: "6rem (96px)" },
      { name: "--space-32", value: "8rem (128px)" }
    ] %}
    {% for token in spacingTokens %}
    <div class="pl-spacing-row">
      <div class="pl-spacing-label">{{ token.name }}<br>{{ token.value }}</div>
      <div class="pl-spacing-bar" style="width: var({{ token.name }})"></div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>


